commit.message:
Add support for setting rest of CURLOPTTYPE_BLOB fields

This adds support for:

- CURLOPT_SSLKEY_BLOB
- CURLOPT_PROXY_SSLCERT_BLOB
- CURLOPT_PROXY_SSLKEY_BLOB
- CURLOPT_ISSUERCERT_BLOB
- CURLOPT_PROXY_ISSUERCERT_BLOB
- CURLOPT_CAINFO_BLOB
- CURLOPT_PROXY_CAINFO_BLOB

Signed-off-by: Vesa Jääskeläinen <vesa.jaaskelainen@vaisala.com>

Add support for setting CURLOPT_SSLCERT_BLOB

This adds support to allow setting of TLS client certificate from memory
instead of file system.

Setting is documented in:
https://curl.se/libcurl/c/CURLOPT_SSLCERT_BLOB.html

Operation takes copy of caller's given str or bytes object making sure
that there are no lingering memory references.

Signed-off-by: Vesa Jääskeläinen <vesa.jaaskelainen@vaisala.com>

commit.message:
Add missing HTTPS proxy options

This commit adds support for:
 * CURLOPT_PROXY_CRLFILE
 * CURLOPT_PROXY_KEYPASSWD
 * CURLOPT_PROXY_PINNEDPUBLICKEY
 * CURLOPT_PROXY_SSLVERSION
 * CURLOPT_PROXY_SSL_CIPHER_LIST
 * CURLOPT_PROXY_SSL_OPTIONS
 * CURLOPT_PROXY_TLSAUTH_TYPE
 * CURLOPT_PROXY_TLSAUTH_USERNAME
 * CURLOPT_PROXY_TLSAUTH_PASSWORD
 * CURLOPT_PROXY_ISSUERCERT

All these options were added in libcurl 7.52.0, except
 CURLOPT_PROXY_ISSUERCERT, which was added in libcurl 7.71.0.
CI: use release version of Python 3.12

commit.message:
Provide generic error strings in pycurl.error objects

If libcurl doesn't provide a specific error string in case of an error,
use curl_easy_strerror() to provide the generic error string
corresponding to a given error code.

Fixes #817.
